Explain:
 Why does Kubernetes use etcd instead of a normal database?
Solution :-
Kubernetes uses etcd because it is designed for distributed systems with strong consistency, which is critical for maintaining cluster state.

# Key Reasons:

• Single Source of Truth
All cluster state (pods, nodes, configs) is stored in etcd. Every component relies on it.

• Strong Consistency (RAFT Algorithm)
Every write is agreed upon by a majority of nodes → no conflicting states.

• Distributed & Fault-Tolerant
Runs across multiple nodes and survives failures.

• Simple Key-Value Store
Kubernetes does not need complex queries (joins, transactions). It only needs fast reads/writes.

• Watch Mechanism (VERY IMPORTANT)
Components “watch” for changes and react instantly (event-driven architecture).

# Key Insight

Kubernetes is a state reconciliation system, not a database-heavy system.
So etcd fits perfectly.
